PLAIN ENGLISH SUMMARY

You are FREE to:

  Use Scrub for any purpose — personal, internal, or commercial
  Study and read the source code
  Copy and distribute it to others
  Modify it and build on top of it
  Use it inside your own products and services

You MUST, if you distribute modified versions:

  Release the complete source code of your modifications
  License your modifications under GPL v3
  State clearly what changes you made
  Keep all copyright and license notices intact

You CANNOT:

  Take this code, modify it, and distribute it as closed-source
  Remove or hide the original copyright notices
  Hold the authors liable for damages

Using Scrub as a tool without modifying and redistributing it does NOT
require you to open source your own code. The copyleft requirement only
applies if you distribute a modified version of Scrub itself.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ORIGIN

Scrub was built after an AWS access key leaked through an AI chat
assistant, causing $10,000 in cloud charges in a single day.

It was open-sourced so no one else has to learn that lesson the
hard way.

